title: How does five-year cancer survival in England vary by cancer type?
analysis_commentary:
The cancers with the lowest five-year survival estimates are mesothelioma (6.6%), pancreatic cancer (6.9%) and brain cancer (11.5%). Testicular cancer (96.8%), melonoma of skin (91.7%) and thyroid cancer (88.5%) have the highest five-year survival estimates.

Updated April 2018.
data_source: Office for National Statistics, Cancer Survival in England
